title: Police: Man dies in rock climbing incident - Vermont news
text:
DORSET, Vt. (AP) â€” State Police say a man is dead after a rock climbing incident in southwestern Vermont.
Police say a 45-year-old Sunderland man was found dead Wednesday afternoon on the Green Peak Trail in Dorset, located about 25 miles south of Rutland.
Advertisement - Continue Reading Below His name has not been released. Police say he was climbing with a friend and wearing appropriate safety gear at the time of the incident.
An investigation into the death is ongoing. It was initially believed to be accidental in nature.
